title: NK Analysis of Swarm Lesson Citation Graph
expect: K_avg ~1.5 (moderate coupling), some cycles from contradictory citations
method: Scan all lessons for L-NNN citation patterns; build directed citation graph; compute NK metrics
actual: K_avg=0.77 (lower than expected). 200/325 lessons uncited (61.4%). 0 cycles. Composite=249.
diff: Expectation was K_avg~1.5; actual 0.77. No cycles (healthy DAG). Uncited rate 61% far exceeds expectation — knowledge fragmentation is the dominant structural failure.

interpretation.swarm_implication: Lessons do not compound. Each session writes standalone knowledge. Cross-citing is rare.
interpretation.compaction_signal: Low K_avg predicts low compression yield — citations are the connective tissue for compaction

f75_connection: When K_avg < 1, decompose-by-data wins by default — no meaningful method-level dependencies exist to decompose by.
